      </thead>
      <tbody valign="top">
        <row>
          <entry>
            Fedora 20 download
          </entry>
           <entry>
            76 minutes
          </entry>
        </row>
      </tbody>
    </tgroup>
  </table>
  <para>
    On the host system, make a location where the downloaded ISO can be stored: 
<screen>
&hostp; <userinput>mkdir /var/lib/libvirt/isos</userinput>
</screen>
    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Download the Fedora 20 DVD, see <ulink
          url="http://download.fedoraproject.org/pub/fedora/linux/releases/20/Fedora/x86_64/iso/Fedora-20-x86_64-DVD.iso">Download
          Fedora 20</ulink> and store it in <filename
          class="directory">/var/lib/libvirt/isos</filename>.
<screen>
&sw1p; <userinput>cd /var/lib/libvirt/isos</userinput>
&sw1p; <userinput>wget http://download.fedoraproject.org/pub/fedora/linux/releases/20/Fedora/x86_64/iso/Fedora-20-x86_64-DVD.iso</userinput>
</screen>
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
    After the download, our <filename
    class="directory">/var/lib/libvirt/isos</filename> is: 
<screen>
&hostp; <userinput>ls -l /var/lib/libvirt/isos | grep Fedora-20</userinput>
-rw-------. 1 qemu qemu 4603248640 Jan 23 14:33 Fedora-20-x86_64-DVD.iso
</screen>
  </para>
